definition.ISO:639:3:eng: User authentication code.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide the username code; if omitted, it will be automatically set with the userâ€™s e-mail.
note.ISO:639:3:eng: Fill this field if you want the user to have a username different from the e-mail.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: User e-mail address.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide the user e-mail address, the field is required.
note.ISO:639:3:eng: The e-mail field is used by default as the unique username.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: User full name.
note.ISO:639:3:eng: You may omit the name, since this information will be provided to the user before the record will be validated.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Group to which the user belongs.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Select the group to which the user will belong.
note.ISO:639:3:eng: When you select a group, if the roles are not yet set, they will be filled with the default roles of the group.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Preferred language of the user.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Set the language in which labels will be displayed for the user.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: User rank or main function.
note.ISO:639:3:eng: The rank represents the main category of the user.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: The roles or functions the user may perform.
note.ISO:639:3:eng: User roles represent the functions that the user is allowed to perform.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: The authentication code.
The authentication password.
Repeat the password
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Repeat the password to confirm it.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide your e-mail address.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: This will be used as your username when you log in.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Select your preferred language.
The rank to which you belong.
The functions and operations you are allowed to perform.
The user that manages your credentials.
The users group to which you belong.
User code or e-mail.
Provide a namespace for the group code.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: This value is used to allow the same group type to belong to several departments.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide a unique code, within the same department, to the group.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: This value is used to uniquely identify a group within a department.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide the group name or label.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: This value will be used as a label or header when displaying groups.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide the group function and scope.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: This value will be visible in popup areas.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide any other relevant information not included in the previous two fields.
Provide the default user roles for the current group.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Group user roles provide a template when creating new users.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: You can use this field to add notes.
